<subSubSection pageId="109" pageNumber="110" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="109.[189,303,1857,1883]" box="[189,303,1857,1883]" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,1857,1883]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,1857,1883]" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="109.[189,1399,1911,2024]" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">
First record from 
<collectingCountry box="[427,545,1911,1937]" name="Denmark" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">Denmark</collectingCountry>
. This species is much larger and significantly less frequent than 
<emphasis box="[189,464,1955,1981]" italics="true" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicName box="[189,460,1955,1981]" class="Laboulbeniomycetes" family="Laboulbeniaceae" genus="Chaetarthriomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Laboulbeniales" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="crassiappendicatus">C. crassiappendicatus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The development of two viable perithecia on the same thallus is exceptional (
<figureCitation box="[199,309,1998,2024]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="108.[189,233,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,378,1890]" captionTargetId="figure-13@108.[189,1399,378,1890]" captionTargetPageId="108" captionText="Fig. 22. Chaetarthriomyces spp. A–B. C. crassiappendicatus Scheloske. Mature thalli with labelled antheridia (arrows). –C–D. C. spiralis Santam. Mature thalli. Scale bars: 50 µm. Photographs from slides ZMUC C-F-123215 (A–B), ZMUC C-F-123214 (C–D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5828990" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5828990/files/figure.png" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">Fig. 22D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
